<dl id="n16012c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n16" href="#n16012c">N16 (VI.D.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n16all.htm#n16012c"> 12(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> language, writing</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In the first place. <mark>Language</mark> not only extends enormously the possibilities of co-operation and common action, but also renders possible the consolidation of customs and their preservation by oral tradition. In the next place, <mark>Writing</mark> enables a society to record all that it considers worth remembering. <small> F.C.S. Schiller, <a name="TANT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TANT"><cite title="source">Tantalus</cite></a> (1924) 25-6</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c02134c" href="c02all.htm#c02134c">VI.C.02:134(c)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
